-- Ghana Defeats 10-Man Serbia 1-0 on Gyan's Penalty in World Cup Group Game
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-13T15:50:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/ghana-defeats-10-man-serbia-1-0-on-gyan-s-penalty-in-world-cup-group-game.html

          
          
             Ghana beat 10-man Serbia 1-0 in the
opening match of Group D at soccer’s World Cup today in
Pretoria, South Africa.  
 Asamoah Gyan scored from the penalty spot in the 84th
minute after Zdravko Kuzmanovic handled the ball. Serbia’s
Aleksandar Lukovic was dismissed in the 74th minute after
receiving a second yellow card.  
 Germany plays Australia in the same group later today.
Slovenia won 1-0 against Algeria in a Group C game.  
          
          


  


        